   Molecular Biology  or CH 301   Physical Chemistry I  and Biochemistry Elective  either CH 321   Structural Biochemistry  or BI 322   Plant Physiology  Students must also complete 4 credits minimum of research experience in an approved area of biology or chemistry  The research experience may be obtained through thesis research  independent research  summer research  a combination of these experiences  or an approved external research experience that offers academic credit  A 2 0 GPA must be maintained in BMB courses for the concentration  An application form for the BMB concentration can be obtained from the Biology Department secretary  or online through the BMB website  Required Courses  you must take these for your BMB concentration  BI 101   General Biology I Credit Hours  4 BI 205   Genetics Credit Hours  4 CH 322   Metabolic Biochemistry Credit Hours  3 CH 323   Laboratory for CH 321 Credit Hours  1 5 Cell Elective  choose one of these  BI 404   Cell Biology Credit Hours  3 or BI 313   Microbiology Credit Hours  4 Molecular Elective  choose one of these  BI 430   Molecular Biology Credit Hours  3 or CH 301   Physical Chemistry I Credit Hours  3 Biochemistry Elective  choose one of these  CH 321   Structural Biochemistry Credit Hours  3 or BI 322   Plant Physiology Credit Hours  4   Back to Top   Print Degree Planner   Print Friendly Page   All catalogues   2016 Virginia Military Institute  Powered by the Acalog  Academic Catalog Management System   ACMS  Mobile Site 